modules.description: This module provides `decode` and `encode` functions for converting between byte arrays and encoding/decoding streams. It operates specifically on `byte_array`, a type alias for a Bigarray of characters in int8 unsigned format. Use it when working with low-level binary data, such as parsing network packets or serializing structured data directly into memory buffers.

This module handles character encoding conversions and low-level encoding/decoding operations. It provides functions to recode strings between different encodings, and to decode bytes into Unicode code points or encode code points into bytes using explicit decoder and encoder types. Concrete use cases include processing text streams in specific encodings, validating encoded byte sequences, and implementing custom text serialization/deserialization logic.
